-- Saudi Court Tries 22 Suspected Al-Qaeda Members, Arab News Says
-- B y   G l e n   C a r e y
-- 2012-04-15T06:56:01Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-15/saudi-court-tries-22-suspected-al-qaeda-members-arab-news-says.html
A Saudi Arabian court began the
trial yesterday of 22 suspected al-Qaeda militants accused of
planning, financing and recruiting for terrorist attacks,  Arab
News  reported, citing the court proceedings.  Twenty-one Saudis and a Bahraini citizen are being tried at
a special criminal court, the Jeddah-based newspaper reported.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Glen Carey in Riyadh at 
 gcarey8@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Andrew J. Barden at 
 barden@bloomberg.net  